[[File:PE-mapa-Palmeirina.png|thumb|right|250px|Location of Palmeirina within Pernambuco.]] [[File:Bandeira palmeirina.gif|thumb|right|160px|Palmeirina's City Flag]] '''Palmeirina''' is a city located in the state of [[Pernambuco]], [[Brazil]]. Located at 252&nbsp;km from [[Recife]], capital of the state of Pernambuco, Palmeirina has an estimated ([[Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics|Ibge 2009]]) population of 8.481 inhabitants.
==Geography== * State - [[Pernambuco]] * Region - [[Agreste|Agreste Pernambucano]] * Boundaries - [[São João, Pernambuco|São João]] and [[Angelim]] ('''N'''); [[Correntes, Pernambuco|Correntes]] and [[Alagoas]] state ('''S'''); [[Canhotinho]] ('''E'''); [[Garanhuns]] ('''W'''). * Area - 158.01&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup> * Elevation - 531 m * Hidrography - [[Mundaú River]] * Vegetation - [[Subperenifólia]] forest * Clima - Hot and humid * Annual average temperature - 22.7 c * Distance to [[Recife]] - 252&nbsp;km
==Economy== The main economic activities in '''Palmeirina''' are based in commerce and [[agribusiness]], especially [[beans]], [[banana]]s; and [[livestock]] such as [[cattle]], [[sheep]] and [[poultry]].
